Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat and add the @lamb mince{200%g}(no oil). Fry 
until browned, breaking it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks, ~{8-10%mins}. Drain 
off any excess fat if necessary.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced). Halve 
the @bell pepper{1}(halved, core and seeds removed). Slice into thin strips. Peel 
and grate the @ginger{½}(peeled and grated). Trim the @courgette{1}(trimmed and quartered 
lengthways). Chop widthways into small pieces.

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. 
When boiling, add a @salt{pinch}, then stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and courgette, 
lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%mins}, 
then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another 
~{10%mins} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

When the lamb has browned, add the onion and pepper. Cook for ~{5%mins}. Add the ginger, 
@Sri Lankan style curry powder{1}(or Sri Lankan curry powder) and @smoked paprika{1}. 
Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @tomato passata{1} and bring to the boil. Lastly add 
the @chicken stock powder{½} and @water for the curry{200%ml}. Lower the heat and simmer 
gently until the liquid has reduced by half, ~{15-20%mins}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). When the curry 
has reduced by half, remove from the heat. Taste the sauce and add @salt{} and @pepper{} 
if necessary. Stir in half the coriander.

Take the lid off the rice and fluff it up with a #fork{}. Season to taste with salt and 
pepper. Spoon the rice onto plates and serve your lamb and coriander curry on top. Finish 
with a sprinkling of remaining coriander. Enjoy!